      <body>
         <listPerson>
            <person sex="1">
               <persName xml:lang="gez" xml:id="n1">አይንቴ፡</persName>
               <persName xml:lang="gez" corresp="#n1" type="normalized">ʾAyǝnte</persName>
               <occupation>mamhǝr</occupation>
               <note>A "mamḥǝre ʾAyǝnte" is pictured in a miniature in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient715">London, British Library, BL Oriental 715</ref> (<locus target="#134r">fol. 134r</locus>) next to
                  <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5617IyasuII">ʾIyāsu II</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS2682BerhanM">Bǝrhān Mogasā</persName>. 
                  A "mamhǝr ʾAyǝnte" is also mentioned in an addition to <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BDLaethb3">Oxford, Bodleian Library, Bodleian Aeth. b. 3</ref> (<locus target="#294ra">fol. 294ra</locus>), in an inventory listing books produced during his tenure.
                  The latter manuscript can be dated to 1730-1755. The uncommon name with identical title used in two manuscripts of the same period makes it likely that both attestations refer 
                  to the same person, but this cannot be determined with absolute certainty.
               </note>
            </person>
            
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text></TEI>